def count_and_say(n: int) -> str:
    if n == 1:
        return '1'
        
    previous = count_and_say(n - 1)
    result = ''
    i = 0
    while i < len(previous):
        j = i
        while j < len(previous) and previous[j] == previous[i]:
            j += 1
        count = str(j - i)
        result += count + previous[i]
        i = j
    return result
